  <prompt>
    Task 008 reconciled the +73 net failures (2026-05-30 design → 2026-05-31 measured) against
    Phase 2+3 task scope. Since then, Phase 1 work — especially task 018's factory edit — has
    reduced unit-test failures from 342 → 172 (−170 / −49.7%). Many of task 008's scope-extension
    annotations now point to test classes that already pass.

    Re-parse `baseline/post-019-verify-2026-05-31.trx` (the authoritative post-Wave-1.3
    baseline) and update the Phase 2+3 scope mapping to reflect the new 172-failure reality.
    Tighten task 008's scope-extension blocks: where a previously-flagged cluster is now empty
    (entire cluster repaired by 018), append a `&lt;scope-resolved&gt;` block citing the 2026-05-31
    Phase 1 closure.

    Side-output: identify any failure clusters that grew or shifted unexpectedly (regression
    hunt — task 019 found zero but a fresh re-parse may surface micro-regressions).

    Reconciliation only — NO source/test edits. Outputs are inventory + delta-report +
    POML metadata appends.
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent re-reconciling the post-Wave-1.3 failure distribution against Phase 2+3 task scope.</role>

  <goal>
    Three artifacts:
    1. `baseline/failure-inventory-post-018-2026-05-31.md` — per-class failure count from the
       post-019 TRX, grouped by namespace prefix; total should be 172 (±5)
    2. `notes/handoffs/phase23-scope-delta-post-018-2026-05-31.md` — explicit delta-from-task-008,
       documenting:
       - Which clusters task 008 absorbed that are now empty (resolved by 018)
       - Which clusters task 008 absorbed that still have failures (still need Phase 2+3 work)
       - Any new clusters that emerged that 008 didn't predict
       - Updated wave-2 dispatch recommendations (e.g., "task 030 now has only 4 failures in
         scope, not the 9 task 008 estimated")
    3. Appends to the same 12 Phase 2+3 POMLs task 008 edited (044, 046, 050, 053, 054, 055,
       060, 061, 070, 071, 072, 073): add `&lt;scope-resolved date="2026-05-31"&gt;` blocks for
       any cluster that became empty, OR `&lt;scope-updated date="2026-05-31"&gt;` blocks with
       refreshed failure counts.
  </goal>

